  "text": "The Kafka consumer fetch request processing chain follows this sequence:\n\n1. **Request Initiation (KafkaConsumer.java:894)**: The user calls `poll(Duration timeout)` which initiates the fetch cycle.\n\n2. **Fetch Request Generation (FetchRequestManager.java)**: The `createFetchRequests()` method creates fetch requests by:\n   - Calling `AbstractFetch.prepareFetchRequests()` (line 412) to prepare request data for each node\n   - Using `AbstractFetch.createFetchRequest()` (line 301) to build the actual FetchRequest.Builder object based on partition assignments and fetch positions\n\n3. **Request Transmission (Fetcher.java)**: The `sendFetches()` method (line 105) sends the built requests via:\n   - `sendFetchesInternal()` (line 184) which calls\n   - `ConsumerNetworkClient.send()` to transmit requests to broker nodes\n\n4. **Network Communication**: `ConsumerNetworkClient.java` manages TCP connections and uses KafkaClient to interact with brokers at the network level.\n\n5. **Response Handling (AbstractFetch.java)**: The `handleFetchSuccess()` method (line 150) processes FetchResponse objects containing `FetchResponseData` with partition data and records.\n\n6. **Buffering (FetchBuffer.java)**: `CompletedFetch` objects are created from the response data and added to the FetchBuffer via the `add()` method (line 97). These represent batches of records from individual partitions.\n\n7. **Record Collection (FetchCollector.java)**: The `collectFetch()` method (line 92) processes the FetchBuffer by:\n   - Iterating through buffered `CompletedFetch` objects\n   - Calling `CompletedFetch.fetchRecords()` (line 252) to deserialize and extract individual ConsumerRecord objects from RecordBatches\n   - Aggregating records into a `Fetch` object (internals/Fetch.java) organized by TopicPartition\n\n8. **Final Result**: The `Fetch` object's records are wrapped into a `ConsumerRecords` object (ConsumerRecords.java) which is returned to the user containing a Map<TopicPartition, List<ConsumerRecord<K, V>>>.\n\nKey classes:\n- **FetchRequest.Builder**: Builds the network request with partition offsets and configurations\n- **FetchResponse/FetchResponseData**: Contains the actual record batches returned from brokers\n- **CompletedFetch**: Wraps a single partition's fetched RecordBatches with state management\n- **FetchCollector**: Converts CompletedFetch objects to ConsumerRecords via deserialization\n- **ConsumerRecords**: The final user-facing container returned from poll()"
}

